<br>
Know why Chanters say their job is hard? Because of maroon Rangers who insist on breaking mez every round. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Enchanters rock. They are not OVERLY powerful on their own, but with some confidence and kick-arse gear (probably why they are considered a &quot;hard&quot; class, you need lots of gear to back you up) they own. I see enchanters all day sitting in Highpass soloing 2 Nobles at a time (yes, ~40th level NPCs) by making them fight eachother. I'd like to see a 50th warrior solo anything even remotely being blue con.<br>
<br>
We've all seen Kaymar with her 135 damage a hit pets in Burning Woods. Imagine the same person sitting in Lower Guk in say a 4 spawn room (Ass/Sup tower for example)... 2 mezzed, 1 charmed, 1 getting it's ass whoopped. Then 1 mezzed, 1 charmed and 1 getting whooped. Then 1 charmed and 1 getting whooped. You get the idea. Hehe.<br>
<br>
